Peter Barth started an accelerator which became The Iron Yard started in Greenville, South Carolina in 2012. He wanted to rejuvenate the area he loved as a high tech location. Eric Dodds joined the group in the Greenville. The team realized there was a lack of development talent for local companies. Mason Stewart was a software engineer doing free coding classes for kid. He was asked to join the team. In 2013, John Saddington also joined the team. 

Iron Yard has 20 campuses in the US and is the largest bootcamp school in the country.
